claim.claim-text:
1. A method for monitoring a cable connection, comprising:
transmitting a local device identifier and a local port identifier associated with a local device;
receiving a remote device identifier and a remote port identifier associated with a remote device;
a port controller determining a status of the cable connection based upon the received remote device identifier and the received remote port identifier; and
a device controller transmitting a status update message to a network management system that includes the local device identifier, the local port identifier, the remote device identifier, the remote port identifier, and the status of the cable connection wherein each of the local and remote devices comprises both the port controller and the device controller.

7. The method of claim 1, wherein:
the local device transmits the local device identifier and the local port identifier to the remote device;
the local device receives the remote device identifier and the remote port identifier from the remote device;
the local device determines the status of the cable connection; and
the local device transmits the status update message to the network management system.
